    "wiki": {
      "title": "Hall effect",
      "extract": "The Hall effect is the production of a potential difference, across an electrical conductor, that is transverse to an electric current in the conductor and to an applied magnetic field perpendicular to the current. Such potential difference is known as the Hall voltage. It was discovered by Edwin Hall in 1879 through a study of the electromagnetic theory of James Clerk Maxwell, becoming a critical confirmation of that theory.",
      "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hall_effect"
    }
  },
